caption: They mess up the occasional cocktail. But the environment is fantastic and it’s a perfect pregame for a movie.

Quaint bar on the highest level of a mini mall.  The atmosphere is really eerie, and unique. Really well furnished. Place is dimly lit and the vibes are really mellow and friendly. Staff was super friendly,  and they make great cocktails. Great spot to end the night,  and grab a few.
Very cool place kinda expensive

Excellent service and delightfully original cocktails make this a fun pit stop on a Friday night out. I recommend their seasonal drink menu which almost always surprises me with it's innovation and affordable price.

The bartenders are good, but the rest of the staff can be extremely rude. Took away our empty glasses in a passive-aggressive maneuver to tell us the bar is closed instead, of well, just politely telling us that. When questioned about this, they sent the bouncer after us, at which point the bartender had to intervene.
Love it! It's quirky and weird and always has great service.
Bartenders were sweet, cool & well versed in their profession. Not easy to come by. As for the drinks? They were divine, I got the non alcoholic ginger mojito & loved every drop.

I've only been here before movies during happy hour. The wait staff is great. Best part is the specials are cheaper than the prices in the theater; and you can take your drinks from the bar to the theater.
Drink were good staff were awesome and nice.

Trendy spot with signature cocktails and creepy( as advertised) wax figures. It's a great spot to pop your head in before or after watching a film. Happy hour specials and HUGE beer selection(41 on draft when I visited).  I will be visiting again.
So spooky and gross
Quirky bar with great cocktails
It a bar  also alil  Expensive to get drinks
Great place to get boozed before the movies :)
Great drinks, good bar snack, cool atmosphere, but slightly overpriced.
best drinks in brooklyn and i absolutely love the staff
Loved it! Totally unique bar experience and comfortable too.

(Translated by Google) Surprising decor, quality service. The place is more planned for lovers' meetings for Americans  (Original) Décor surprenant, service de qualité. L'endroit est plus prévue pr des rencontres d'amoureux pr les américains
The drinks are fine enough, and the service is just impossible. It can be tricky to come in before a movie because it takes such a long time to get a check.

Super cool wax pieces! I had a Chai Fighter beverage - hot tea with bourbon, served with a cookie. It was perfect for a snowy day and the Star Wars theme was cool too. Fun place to wait before heading to the Alamo.
A little weird, a little quirky, a little pricy but a fun place to bring your friends.
Interesting but weird.
Stick with beer. I doubt the "bartender" could make a glass of ice water. The intrigue of the wax figures didn't hold my attention as i walked out in disappoint.

This is one of my favorite bars in Brooklyn, and not just because it’s conveniently located in the same building as Trader Joe’s and Target and Alamo. It is a really cool bar - the artifacts are fascinating to look at on their own. On top of that, the drink menu is so cool, with drinks from the early 20th century and the 19th century - and they’re delicious. The service is great, you can carry your drinks up to your movie, or you can get tipsy before your target trip. Either way, this place is great. Highly recommend.
best!!
Awesome!!!!!!!
Great for hook ups
Creepy but awesome pretzels and drinks!
Love it. Very macabre, very dark. Nice cocktail list. There are no signs that I saw but it's on the 4th floor of DeKalb market.
Such a different and unique must-see NY bar!! It also helps when you have an awesome bartender like Cody!!
Friendly service, good drinks and an interestingly strange atmosphere.
Delicious!

We visited Brooklyn to visit friends. At their suggestion we stopped in for a quick drink and to check out the macabre wax sculptures. My girl and our hosts enjoyed the ‘Mature’ was sculptures and historical ‘lessons’ they provided. Although our hosts only wanted to stay for one, my girl and I had two, they were just that good. I had a Brooklyn which had a few different varieties and she had the Dead Horse Bay. I will be back next time I’m in the area. 4 stars because we didn’t eat there.
Low key great beer selection and you can take it upstairs to your movie. Also there's a great bartender spinning new wave that kills it
Very cool place!
This is one of my hang outs. Definately recommend it.
Loved the art work, the scenery, awesome drinks and stsff
Great drinks and atmosphere!
(Translated by Google) I loved  (Original) Me encanto
It is like having beers at a museum
Spooky bar with wax statues and decapitated heads, a movie buff will love it.
Nice place
Chill atmosphere, great music, acceptable service. There's a small food menu which has great options - the chips & queso is excellent!
Super cool horror-esque decor. Massive beer list. Worth coming here even if you're not seeing a movie
Must try the cauliflower here !!
Cool and spooky atmosphere.  Great cocktails !

I almost fainted bc my blood pressure dropped and the bartender literally came to me and said “Don’t sleep on the bar because it’s super rude!” I was sick and almost fainted and he thought that it was rude?!! I even talked to the manager and she didn’t even bother to apologize! She said it was miscommunication and she was so uncaring and not interested to hear what I’ve to hear! I’m contacting the owner to know how much his staff is rude with sick ppl! I’ve never been treated so badly like today! I used to love and recommend this bar to all my friends.. now hell I’d never recommend anyone bc your safety is their last concern!
Pretzels are on point
Friendly staff and sultry, low light vibes--very relaxing hideaway compared to the rest of City Point.  Always an outstanding beer selection.   Great for fans of IPAs and sours!

Legendary place. You gotta take the elevator to the 4th floor, if lost ask for the Alamo Drafthouse. Anyhow legendary cocktails and great vibes. So happy we went here. Fast and friendly service we had a great time. Recommendation... Get the prince regent of Bavaria for your European twist on a long island iced tea.
Waitress handed us menus then never returned. Water was refreshing but I'd rather have a beer.
Spooky atmosphere but fun. Good cocktails
Can get a bit crowded but it's a nice environment to have some drinks before/after a flick at the Alamo. They even have a staff member come by and let you know when they're seating for a movie.
So cool.
Drinks was the bomb

Nice selection of beers and cocktails. The bar staff are friendly and helpful. It's located inside the Alamo Drafthouse cinema so it's a nice place to go before or after a screening, or even just for a drink. The decor and atmosphere is unique and worth a/several visits.
Super interesting place with top notch waiters and bartenders serving a huge variety of cocktail drinks. Also live DJs and beautiful waxes of classical characters. Not for the faint hearted.
Love the variety of beer and fantastic service!
Great drinks, great decor.
It was a super weird and cool place to get a drink

This would be an awesome be if it were either a) chilled and relaxed with expensive drinks or b) crowded and lively with inexpensive drinks. Unfortunately it is crowded and loud. Not a great place to wait until your movie starts or sit and talk about the movie you just saw. Idk. Might be a good place to meet before a blind date or awkward 2nd date you're not sure you want to be on. Maybe get up to use the restroom and never come back?

A bar and wax museum wrapped up into one located in the back of the lobby of the Alamo Drafthouse in Downtown Brooklyn. Not for the faint of heart or those with a weak stomach. The prices are those of a upscale Manhattan bar.  I do love hanging out here even if I don't see a movie.
Great local beers on tap and staff is very attentive
Great and cozy, but the masks made me queasy
Service is tough due to the ebs and flows of people attending movies, but overall it's a solid place
Good drinks, good vibe.

I usually go to this bar before or after seeing a show at Alamo Drafthouse. Only here could you get a drink and look at a bunch of cool wax sculptures. But be warned some of them are pretty intense looking.

Love this spot. Everything is really great . . . I always forget where I am in the city when I visit. Pretty good music and really good drinks. Only issue is that if you go before a movie there may be people talking about that same movie. So spoiler alert. But other than that, one of the best if not only bars in the area.

This place is inside the Alamo Drafthouse lobby and a good place to grab some drinks and light snack before your movie. Prices are steep but this place isn't meant to spend a whole night at. The wax museum inside is really cool and definitely worth checking out
Great service.  New drinks seasonally and daily.
Dark and disturbing in good way. Great friendly service. Will be back.
Great drinks and fun atmosphere! If you want something out-of-the-box, definitely recommend!
Such a great creepy weird atmosphere & awesome friendly bartender!!! I love this spot  Dark and stormy was so spicy with the real ginger instead of ginger beer.. it was tough to drink

Weird and fun. This bar is decorated in a dark gothic fashion, with grotesque medical models made of wax. If you ever wanted to drink in a table that houses a wax fetus, this is your chance. This is inside the Alamo Drafthouse so you'll have to walk through the lobby to enter. Happy hour for cocktails and beer.

The restaurant is extremely dishonest. On the receipts they put a percentage scale like 15% 18% 20% and 22%. My order was $20 and instead of seeing $4 as the suggested tip for 20% they put $6.50. I understand trying to get more money for your servers but when you treat your customers like they're idiots and then lie to them through the receipts it's unacceptable and a horrible business practice.
Very cool and creepy place.A little bit hard to find at first.
Spooky.
Unique atmosphere, went there on a first date, the place certainly made the conversation more interesting. I highly recommend it!
Amazing cocktails,  read the ingredients!
Really cool place!
Creepy wax figures that are mind boggling.  Check out the hermaphrodites.  Drinks are wonderful and the staff full of knowledge
Good cocktails. Lolita sculpture kinda concerning. Bought some notebooks at Crouching Tiger. 5/5 would go to the food hall.

I like this place it's very dark and out of the way. I think they successfully made the place seem like it's not in a movie theater. The wax figures are kinda crazy there is alot of sex organs everywhere in the back if your into that. Drinks and beers are good with a very large selection.
Must go spot for goths and alt ppl! Amazing and creepy place with nice cocktails.
Awesome atmosphere. Great to go before the movie starts or after. Or simply for the nice cocktails or large selection of craft beer.
So gruesome and nice! And the drinks are top notch.
Very unique bar!! Loved it! And you can have your drinks taken to the movie theater!

Love this bar. It's a hidden little thing, but the drink selection is fantastic. Usually some funky stuff on tap, which any beer lover will appreciate. The figures are definitely creepy, which can be a positive or negative thing depending on who you're with. Come for a drink–the bartenders are fantastic.
Crowded, loud and slow service. For eh food and drinks, would be better if you went to the bottom floor to trader Joe's for food and drinks.
Great cocktails; didn't try the food though
Amazing bar. Staff are great, drinks are imaginative. Location is an upper floor of a shopping mall, so, it does seem a bit out of place. Very worth the visit. Atmosphere is astounding!
Good set of cocktails as well as craft beers. And macabre wax fixtures give it a unique look.
Best bar service ever. These people are amazing!

Less a wax museum, more of a movie theater bar with food and creepy decor. Dim lit interior, drinks were well made and promptly served, but will not substitute for Madame Toussauds. Good for pre /post movie libations for sure.
Weird, creepy, cool decor. There are some pretty gruesome wax sculptures here. Drinks are on the expensive side.
So much fun

Creepy cool decor. Nice place to stop and pre-gane before watching a flick at The Alamo. Good food and good drinks. Pricey but that’s to be expected from the location. Staff was friendly but not very attentive.
The babies r cool and scary
Hidden gem! Fantastic service and cocktails!

The wax museum is sooooooo cool. They are really old wax sculptures with really weird and gross things. Think infant deformation. Transgendered parts. Organs moved from wearing a corset. Cool and weird. They have a zillion beers on tap and about 6 ciders Which is always a plus for me!!!! Will be back here and try for some drink shopping afterwards.
Place rules!
Weird. Just how I like it.
creepy place, great cocktails. i wish it served actual food.
Terrible and lazy customer service. Beautiful decor but come on....
Will definitely be back! Great service and awesome atmosphere! If you are in the Brooklyn area you must stop in!
It's a bit creepy and weird. Conversation starter to say the least. It was hard to get too comfortable given the nature of the wax figures. Some of it was disturbing.

This bar is inside the Alamo Draft House. I love the atmosphere, the wax figure decorations are cool. Really good and extensive beer list. If you are a beer fan you should check this place out. I didn't try the cocktails but they looked good.
possibly my favourite bar in new York these days

This place is a comedy club that is filled with death masks of people! I'll give you a moment to take that in.... But, it has an amazing selection of beer and really happy staff. So would definitely recommend this place!

This was the first time I was here. The concept of this bar is really cool and is modeled off "entertainment" in the late 19th century. There is an extensive drink list but a small food list. Definitely visit here before going to see a movie at the Alamo Draft House.

Great place to take visitors from out of town--love the macabre collection that constitutes the decor!  Strictly as a bar, it falls slightly short of the high bar set by local favorites, but the fact that it's in a movie theater?  Are you kidding?  Awesome!
Definitely a creative spot with an excellent selection of beer
The free museum alone is worth visiting, but while you're there definitely enjoy a novelty cocktail or one of the 48 draft beer options (all from NY state).
Great selection of NY beers, friendly staff (that should be able to work out the initial week of operations kinks) and good vibe inside. Exactly what the Downtown Brooklyn scene needs at the moment.
